13:19.367 --> 13:20.300
story, right?

13:20.300 --> 13:21.100
Sure.

13:21.100 --> 13:23.267
In 1996, I was convicted of a

13:23.267 --> 13:24.467
first-time, non-violent

13:24.467 --> 13:25.133
drug crime.

13:25.133 --> 13:26.600
I was sentenced to ten years in

13:26.600 --> 13:28.733
prison, spent almost four years

13:28.733 --> 13:30.467
there, and once I got out, I was

13:30.467 --> 13:32.267
able to get my education, get my

13:32.267 --> 13:34.067
bachelor's degree, law degree.

13:34.067 --> 13:35.367
I'm licensed to practice law in

13:35.367 --> 13:36.300
two different states.

13:36.300 --> 13:37.467
Been even honored at the

13:37.467 --> 13:39.033
White House by the president.

13:39.033 --> 13:40.467
But I still can't vote in my

13:40.467 --> 13:41.233
home state.

13:41.233 --> 13:43.133
And this doesn't just affect me.

13:43.133 --> 13:44.467
Because African Americans are

13:44.467 --> 13:46.067
disproportionately arrested for

13:46.067 --> 13:48.400
non-violent crimes, 13% of

13:48.400 --> 13:49.767
African American males in this

13:49.767 --> 13:51.367
country can't vote because of

13:51.367 --> 13:52.967
felon disenfranchisement laws.

13:52.967 --> 13:54.633
The bottom line is, Jim Crow

13:54.633 --> 13:56.133
laws that are still on the books

13:56.133 --> 13:58.200
are stopping 5 million Americans

13:58.200 --> 13:59.467
like Daryl from voting

13:59.467 --> 14:00.633
every year.

14:00.633 --> 14:01.633
It's deplorable.

14:01.633 --> 14:02.433
I agree.

14:02.433 --> 14:03.633
I gotta run, guys.

14:03.633 --> 14:04.467
Thank you, Daryl.

14:04.467 --> 14:06.367
Come on.

14:06.367 --> 14:07.933
We need to do something.

14:07.933 --> 14:09.467
We need to extend the vote to

14:09.467 --> 14:10.933
those people.

14:10.933 --> 14:11.800
I know!

14:11.800 --> 14:12.867
I'll vote for a candidate who

14:12.867 --> 14:14.133
