19:15.633 --> 19:16.900
But, I wanted to come tell you,

19:16.900 --> 19:17.967
don't lose heart, Donna.

19:17.967 --> 19:19.233
The founding fathers said "All

19:19.233 --> 19:20.900
men are created equal," and they

19:20.900 --> 19:21.967
couldn't live up to it in their

19:21.967 --> 19:23.900
era, but they built a machine

19:23.900 --> 19:25.433
that allows us to get better

19:25.433 --> 19:26.300
every generation.

19:26.300 --> 19:27.133
Now, it's our turn.

19:27.133 --> 19:28.800
Look, American democracy

19:28.800 --> 19:30.633
isn't perfect, but it used to be

19:30.633 --> 19:32.200
a lot worse, and our system is

19:32.200 --> 19:33.767
actually more inclusive and

19:33.767 --> 19:35.900
democratic than it has ever

19:35.900 --> 19:36.800
been before.

19:36.800 --> 19:38.300
And that's because, we've used

19:38.300 --> 19:40.433
democracy to make democracy

19:40.433 --> 19:41.233
stronger.

19:41.233 --> 19:42.567
So, Donna, if you want things to

19:42.567 --> 19:44.633
get better, you have to vote.

19:44.633 --> 19:46.133
I guess, but changing the

19:46.133 --> 19:48.033
system seems really hard.

19:48.033 --> 19:49.633
Oh, it is, but here's one

19:49.633 --> 19:50.933
simple idea-- why don't we make

19:50.933 --> 19:53.300
election day a national holiday?

19:53.300 --> 19:54.600
It's way too difficult for busy

19:54.600 --> 19:56.100
Americans to get to the polls.

19:56.100 --> 19:57.033
Tell me about it.

19:57.033 --> 19:58.067
I had to take off work

19:58.067 --> 19:59.433
to come here.

19:59.433 --> 20:00.733
That way, more Americans

20:00.733 --> 20:02.533
could vote more easily, and we

20:02.533 --> 20:03.967
would have time to celebrate

20:03.967 --> 20:05.900
election day for what it is--

20:05.900 --> 20:07.300
the most patriotic day of

20:07.300 --> 20:07.967
the year.

20:07.967 --> 20:09.367
What an awesome idea, Adam.

20:09.367 --> 20:11.367
You know, that really is

20:11.367 --> 20:13.133
inspiring.

20:13.133 --> 20:13.967
I'll do it!

20:13.967 --> 20:16.133
I'll vote!

20:16.133 --> 20:18.300
(softly) Yeah.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.733
Oh, hey, Donna, um...

20:19.733 --> 20:21.367
I really liked traveling through

20:21.367 --> 20:22.133
time with you.

20:22.133 --> 20:23.867
Oh, me too.

20:23.867 --> 20:24.767
And any time you want to have

20:24.767 --> 20:27.233
tea, or chat, or just hang out,

20:27.233 --> 20:28.233
you know, let me know.

20:28.233 --> 20:29.067
Hang out?

20:29.067 --> 20:31.200
Like... as friends?

20:31.200 --> 20:32.733
Mr. Conover, I would love to

20:32.733 --> 20:33.633
be your friend.

20:33.633 --> 20:38.600
♪♪

20:38.600 --> 20:39.533
Want to come over tonight

20:39.533 --> 20:40.267
and make spaghetti?

20:40.267 --> 20:41.233
I'm kind of busy.

20:41.233 --> 20:43.200
Maybe some other time.

20:43.200 --> 20:44.300
Great. (chuckling)

20:44.300 --> 20:45.633
That's great.

20:45.633 --> 20:47.133
Literally, any night works

20:47.133 --> 20:48.133
for me.

20:48.133 --> 20:54.167
♪♪

20:56.133 --> 20:56.800
Next time, on

20:56.800 --> 20:57.933
"Adam Ruins Everything..."

20:57.933 --> 20:59.033
You are literally working your

20:59.033 --> 21:00.400
employees stupid.

21:00.400 --> 21:01.233
How much money do you make?

21:01.233 --> 21:01.900
Unh!

21:01.900 --> 21:02.700
If you don't know what the going

21:02.700 --> 21:04.133
rate is for your salary, it's

21:04.133 --> 21:05.433
easier for the company to rip

21:05.433 --> 21:06.267
you off.

21:06.267 --> 21:07.267
I demand a raise!
